=== Description===
"Common Ground can function very effectively as a physical place where responsible individuals can create a match between their needs and the collective needs of the area. They can create space for an unprecedented enterpreneurship which is not bound by the pure creation of 'monetary' value. The synergy created between different forms of value  can help solve the obvious inadequacy of the market and the government in creating real well-being, based on sustainable solutions for the future. Bright Futures will build a bridge between the reality of the speculative market and the Flemish land scarcity at one site and the desire and the willingness of many to freely co-invest in a better future."



